# OOP Property Model (Python)

This project demonstrates core Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts in Python by modeling different types of properties and buyer preferences.

### Classes Included
- **House** Base class defining shared property attributes.
- **Bungalow** Subclass representing single-story houses.
- **Apartments**  Subclass representing apartments with optional amenities.
- **HouseBuyerPreference**  Represents a buyerâ€™s ideal property and spending budget.

### Concepts Demonstrated
- Inheritance and subclass specialization
- Encapsulation (private attributes)
- Constructor overriding with `super()`
- Object instantiation and attribute access
